│ poison if the shift amount is greater than or equal to the bitwidth of the element. For i1 elements, any shift amount of 1 is poison. The original code shifts <2 x i32> by <2 x i32> and │
│ is well-defined (e.g., shifting 0/1 values), but after the transform, a dynamic shift amount of 1 becomes poison, which is incorrect. The fix is to make VectorCombine only perform this  │
